Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
start_parallel_edit(25.10)                          start_parallel_edit(25.10)

Name
       start_parallel_edit  - Initializes parallel editing by drawing a yellow
       square on the main window to indicate the  edit  area  and  saving  the
       physical  data,  net  attributes,  via cell names and Non-Default Rules
       (NDRs) to a multiple binary files

Syntax
       start_parallel_edit

       [-help]

       [-area_restricted]

       -region {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}

       Initializes parallel editing by drawing a yellow  square  on  the  main
       window  to indicate the edit area and saving the physical data, net at-
       tributes, via cell names and Non-Default Rules (NDRs) to a multiple bi-
       nary files.

       Once the DRC edits are complete,  the  parallel  edit  session  can  be
       stopped by using the end_parallel_edit command.

       Note: If the design is freed up from the current session, the edit ses-
       sion is terminated automatically.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each start_parallel_edit parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man start_parallel_edit

       -area_restricted
              Writes  out  only  the  different objects inside or touching the
              specified edit area. This is a strict interpretation of the  re-
              gion, and ignores the changes made outside of the region.

       -region {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies the coordinates of the edit area.

Example
              * The  following command marks the specified edit area in yellow
                and saves the design data to binary files:

                innovus  8>   start_parallel_edit   -area_restricted   -region
                {12.524 6.627 0.0 0.0}

